&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Appointment for Service STR in Infectious Diseases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Sheffield Laboratory Medicine Directorate seeks to appoint a LAS Registrar in Infectious Diseases for a period of 6 months in the first instance (possible extension may be available) commencing as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will involve out of hours work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any candidate who is unable for personal reasons to work full-time will be eligible to be considered for the post; if such a person is appointed, modification of the job content will be discussed on a personal basis with the Trust in consultation with consultant colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAnne TunbridgeAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about the post please contact Dr A Tunbridge, Training programme Director for Infectious Diseases anne.tunbridge1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
